2026-04-25T15:12:11.801Z JOY-011D-C9 comment.added "Plan: replace 'joy completions bash' output with a colon-aware dynamic wrapper. Steps in the wrapper: (1) read COMP_WORDS verbatim, (2) walk and merge any token group that contains ':' (e.g. ['ai:', '', 'claude'] -> ['ai:claude']), tracking the corrected COMP_CWORD, (3) call the clap_complete bash protocol with the merged words via env vars, (4) for each returned candidate that has the same colon-prefix as the (merged) current word, emit just the post-colon-prefix suffix so bash inserts only the difference. Static completion stays available via 'joy completions bash --static'. zsh/fish unchanged." [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-04-25T15:30:48.550Z JOY-011D-C9 comment.added "[x] joy completions bash now emits a colon-aware dynamic wrapper. The wrapper walks COMP_WORDS, merges any group separated by ':' (e.g. ['ai:', '', 'claude'] -> ['ai:claude']) while tracking COMP_CWORD, calls the clap_complete bash protocol with the merged words, and strips the colon-prefix from each candidate so bash inserts only the post-colon suffix. [x] Tests with the new wrapper: ai:<TAB> -> [claude@joy, copilot@joy, qwen@joy, vibe@joy]; ai:cl<TAB> -> [claude@joy]; ai<TAB> -> [ai:claude@joy, ...]; -m h<TAB> -> [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]. [x] Static script available via 'joy completions bash --static-only' for the legacy behavior. [x] Help text mentions 'set completion-ignore-case on' for users who want fully case-insensitive completion (a readline setting, not joy-specific). [x] just check green end-to-end (270 lib + 2 trycmd + 184 bats)." [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
